Name: libpng
URL: https://github.com/pnggroup/libpng
Original URL: https://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html
Version: 1.6.58
Revision: 3061454d980de7d53608f594194cfac722721d2a
Security Critical: yes
License Android Compatible: yes

License File: src/LICENSE
  License: Libpng

Description:
  Updated to 1.6.58, stripped all unneeded files.

  - Strip all unneeded files
  rm -r ci contrib projects scripts tests \
  ANNOUNCE CHANGES INSTALL TODO autogen.sh configure.ac CMakeLists.txt Makefile.am \
  aclocal.m4 compile config.guess config.sub configure depcomp install.sh ltmain.sh \
  missing test-driver libpng-manual.txt .github .editorconfig .editorconfig-checker.json \
  *.in *.3 *.5 *.png *.jpg *.dfa *.yaml

  - Use custom configuration file pnglibconf.h, which turns off features that
  are not in use.
  - Configures custom png chunk user limits (crbug.com/117369) in pnglibconf.h.
  Revision is from `git merge-base JIRI_HEAD v1.6.58`.

Local Modifications:
See https://fxbug.dev/526720299 for details.

The dependency is a fork of a large library, reduced to just two files - a
header and a .cc file, which has then been adapted to work on Fuchsia.

The full library is present and regularly maintained at //third_party/icu.
However, it is not appropriate for the fxl library to take on this large
dependency for the very limited piece of functionality it actually uses.

As a result of adaptation, and almost total strip-down,
//src/lib/fxl/third_party/icu has taken on a new life as a fuchsia-specific
library, with adequate functionality which effectively did not need to be
modified in the last ~10 years.

With that in mind, the library should be exempted for freshness because it is a
stand-alone library which has not had new commits since it was placed in
service. Yes, it is unusual for a piece of software to stop changing, but this
library is "complete".

